dc_title_s: The Balkans 1:250,000. Larisa, sheet G-5. A.M.S. M506 (G.S.G.S. 4410)
dc_description_s: Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4410. Alternate title: Larisa, Greece. Universal transverse Mercator and Mediterranean zone grids. Principal meridians are Athens and Greenwich. UTM grid added, gradient tints and air information deleted by AMS, 1948. UTM grid values revised, 1950. Relief shown by 100 meter contour intervals and elevations. Compiled by 512 Fd. Survey Coy. R. E. Feb. 1944. With a Greek glossary. See index. Library holdings for this set are incomplete.
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1950.
